text: Les Hauts de Forterre is a commune in the department of Yonne, central France, in the natural region of Forterre. The municipality was established on 1 January 2017 by merger of the former communes of Taingy (the seat), Fontenailles and Molesmes.Arrêté préfectoral 16 August 2016 == See also == *Communes of the Yonne department == References == Category:Communes of Yonne
title: Les Hauts de Forterre
